From: R9700 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-11
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_mm: add per-expert AWQ/GPTQ load mapping

`Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration.load_weights` (the multimodal entry-class
load path used for gemma-4-26B-A4B-it-AWQ-GPTQ-v2-fixed and the
mattbucci/gemma-4-26B-AWQ HF mirror) only had a fused-BF16 expert weight
mapping (`experts.gate_up_proj` → `experts.w13_weight`).  Per-expert
AWQ checkpoint keys (`experts.0.gate_proj.qweight`,
`experts.0.up_proj.qweight`, etc.) silently failed to match anything,
leaving `experts.w13_qweight` at random init.  Result: layer-0 MoE
forward returns NaN, NaN cascades through every subsequent layer, lm_head
produces all-NaN logits, sampler crashes with `HSAIL 0x1016` in
`sampler.py:498` on first inference.

This patch adds the per-expert mapping that already exists in
`Gemma4ForCausalLM.load_weights` (gemma4_causal.py lines ~1011-1027) but
was missing from the multimodal entry class.  The mapping uses
`FusedMoE.make_expert_params_mapping(...)` to enumerate per-expert tuples
and is checked BEFORE the fused-BF16 mapping (so AWQ checkpoints take
priority when both formats are configured).

Required for AWQ-quantized Gemma 4 26B MoE on R9700.  Companion to:
- patches/023 (gemma4-moe-mlp-no-quant-config) — dense MLP load path
- patches/024 (gemma4-mm-towers-no-quant-config) — vision tower BF16
- patches/033 (moe-wna16-gelu-activation) — gelu activation in moe_wna16
- launch.sh QUANT="moe_wna16" — forces AWQ MoE method dispatch

Root-caused 2026-05-11 via top-down NaN bisect.  See memory file
project_gemma4_v0511_root_cause.md for the full chain.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_mm.py
@@ -741,9 +741,30 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(PreTrainedModel):
     def load_weights(self, weights: Iterable[Tuple[str, torch.Tensor]]):
+        from sglang.srt.layers.moe.fused_moe_triton.layer import FusedMoE
+
         k_eq_v_layers = self._get_k_eq_v_layers()

         num_experts = getattr(self.config.text_config, "num_experts", 0) or 0
+        # Per-expert mapping for AWQ/GPTQ checkpoints (experts.0.gate_proj.qweight, …).
+        # Without this, AWQ-quantized expert weights silently fail to load — the
+        # FusedMoE param `experts.w13_qweight` stays at empty/random init, the
+        # MoE forward at layer 0 returns NaN, and the LM head produces all-NaN
+        # logits → HSAIL 0x1016 in sampler.py:498 on first inference.
+        # Same shape as the per-expert mapping in Gemma4ForCausalLM.load_weights;
+        # this multimodal entry class was missing it. Root-caused 2026-05-11.
+        per_expert_params_mapping = (
+            FusedMoE.make_expert_params_mapping(
+                ckpt_gate_proj_name="gate_proj",
+                ckpt_down_proj_name="down_proj",
+                ckpt_up_proj_name="up_proj",
+                num_experts=num_experts,
+            )
+            if num_experts > 0
+            else []
+        )
+        # Fused mapping for BF16 checkpoints (experts.gate_up_proj [E, 2*I, H]).
         expert_params_mapping = [
             # (param_name, ckpt_weight_name, shard_ids)
             # gate_up_proj is fused [E, 2*I, H] — chunk into w1 (gate) + w3 (up)
@@ -770,6 +791,30 @@ class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(PreTrainedModel):
             # MoE expert weights checked first (gate_up_proj contains "up_proj"
             # which would false-match the stacked dense MLP mapping).
             orig_name = name
+
+            # --- Per-expert AWQ/GPTQ weights (experts.{i}.gate_proj.qweight) ---
+            is_expert_weight = False
+            for param_name, weight_name, expert_id, shard_id in per_expert_params_mapping:
+                if weight_name not in name:
+                    continue
+                is_expert_weight = True
+                name = name.replace(weight_name, param_name)
+                if name not in params_dict:
+                    continue
+                param = params_dict[name]
+                weight_loader = param.weight_loader
+                weight_loader(
+                    param, loaded_weight, name,
+                    shard_id=shard_id, expert_id=expert_id,
+                )
+                break
+            else:
+                if is_expert_weight:
+                    loaded_params.add(name)
+                    continue
+            if is_expert_weight:
+                loaded_params.add(name)
+                continue
+
